			</li>								<li>									In <a href="2">Part 2</a>,									hardships from the still-unstable environment of Niarba lead eventually to war between the rival factions, with Lievus and Kadia regretfully on opposite sides.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="2/1">Episode 1</a>,											the offshoot colony under Kadia's leadership grows larger more rapidly than the first colony of survivors, breeding worries in the older original population.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/2">Episode 2</a>,											still further offshoot colonies branch off of Kadia's colony, and she and Lievus work together to maintain unity of their growing and fragmenting people.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/3">Episode 3</a>,											a terrible year plunges the newer colonies into chaos, threatening a war of which Kadia and Lievus reluctantly find themselves on opposite sides.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="3">Part 3</a>,									Lievus' faction emerges victorious in the war, after he remorsefully slays Kadia in a titanic duel, and her children lead the surviving "warlocks" into the wilderness.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="3/1">Episode 1</a>,											attempts at negotiation to prevent hostile actions fail as the opposing sides of the conflict grow ever more polarized, and violence proves inevitable.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/2">Episode 2</a>,											the violence of the war comes to a head as Lievus is forced to kill Kadia in a duel, and her family and chief supporters flee into the wilderness.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/3">Episode 3</a>,											surviving magic users find themselves a minority in the aftermath of the war, and the last attempts at mainaining unity of the Ehrban people are abandoned.										</li>									</ol>								</li>							</ol>						</li>					</ol>				</section><? require $_SERVER['DOCUMENT_ROOT'] . "/includes/footer-global.php" ?>